		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "In this paper , we propose a joint model for unsupervised Chinese word segmentation ( CWS ) . <S>",
			"relation": "ROOT"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "Inspired by the \"products of experts\" idea , ",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "our joint model firstly combines two generative models , ",
			"relation": "elab-process_step"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "which are word-based hierarchical Dirichlet process model and character-based hidden Markov model , ",
			"relation": "elab-enum_member"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 3,
			"text": "by simply multiplying their probabilities together . <S>",
			"relation": "manner-means"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 9,
			"text": "Gibbs sampling is used for model inference . <S>",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "In order to further combine the strength of goodness-based model , ",
			"relation": "enablement"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "we then integrated nVBE into our joint model ",
			"relation": "elab-process_step"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 8,
			"text": "by using it to initializing the Gibbs sampler . <S>",
			"relation": "manner-means"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 13,
			"text": "We conduct our experiments on PKU and MSRA datasets ",
			"relation": "manner-means"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 10,
			"text": "provided by the second SIGHAN bakeoff . <S>",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 13,
			"text": "Test results on these two datasets show ",
			"relation": "attribution"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "that the joint model achieves much better results than all of its component models . <S>",
			"relation": "evaluation"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 15,
			"text": "Statistical significance tests also show ",
			"relation": "attribution"
		},
		{
			"id": 15,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "that it is significantly better than state-of-the-art systems , ",
			"relation": "evaluation"
		},
		{
			"id": 16,
			"parent": 15,
			"text": "achieving the highest F-scores . <S>",
			"relation": "elab-addition"
		},
		{
			"id": 17,
			"parent": 19,
			"text": "Finally , analysis indicates ",
			"relation": "attribution"
		},
		{
			"id": 18,
			"parent": 19,
			"text": "that compared with nVBE and HDP , ",
			"relation": "comparison"
		},
		{
			"id": 19,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "the joint model has a stronger ability ",
			"relation": "evaluation"
		},
		{
			"id": 20,
			"parent": 19,
			"text": "to solve both combinational and overlapping ambiguities in Chinese word segmentation . <S>",
